TERM: III
TOPIC 34:
APPLIED CHEMISTRY
DURATION:
12 Periods
GENERAL OBJECTIVE:
By the end of this topic the learner should be able to appreciate the importance and application of
Chemistry in every day life.
SUB-TOPIC
SPECIFIC OBJECTIVE
CONTENT
Water resource
pollution
(7 periods)
Learners should be able to:
State industrial and domestic uses
of water.
State the causes of water pollution.
Define hard and soft water
Outline the methods of removing
water hardness
Describe water treatment process.
Describe the methods of sewage
treatment
Outline the products of sewage
treatment.
Industrial and domestic uses of
water.
Causes of water pollution
- Pollution from fertilizers,
insecticides and others.
Agricultural wastes. (only the
pollution aspects)
Oil pollution of the sea and
lakes, the dispersal of oil slicks.
Hard and soft water
Definition
Causes of hard water
- Removal of hardness (temporary
and permanent hardness, include
ion exchange method).
Water treatment: filtration,
fluoridation and desalination,
Sewage: methods of sewage
treatment; production of
biogas(methane) and fertilizers.
TEACHING AND LEARNING
STRATEGIES
Discussion domestic and
industrial uses of water.
Assign the learners group
work on causes of water
pollution.
Discuss the definitions of
hard and soft water.
Discuss the causes of hard
water and how to remove
hardness in water.
Conduct a field trip to a water
treatment plant.
Conduct a field trip to a
sewage treatment plant.
